## Summary

**What changed:** `scripts/preseed_session_plan.py` line 423 — replaced substring `any(word in lower ...)` check with `re.search(r'\b(?:flaky|fail|failed|error|retry)\b', lower)` in `_self_tests_show_resolution()`.

**Why:** The substring match `"fail" in lower` matched `"failure"` inside `"last-failure"`, causing self-test lines like `why last-failure → correct ✅` to be skipped. This made the preseed picker blind to already-satisfied tasks (like cold-start diagnostics), wasting ~20% of sessions on stale tasks.

**Verification:**
• Regression case `_self_tests_show_resolution('why last-failure → correct ✅', ('why last-failure',))` now returns `True` ✓
• Standalone `"fail"`, `"failed"`, `"error"`, `"flaky"`, `"retry"` still correctly excluded ✓
• `"failure"` and `"failures"` now correctly detected as resolved ✓
• `python3 scripts/preseed_session_plan.py --test` passes ✓
• `cargo fmt -- --check` passes ✓

